UML:TaggedValue.value: automatic or semi-automatic application by a machine
a pathological condition that affects part or all of production in the Plot
a human need to apply a fertilizer to soil
a plant or animal detrimental to a human
to reduce plants considered undesirable in a particular situation

unique identification, e.g. e.g. MCHN005, of a machine applying the Treatment; such unique identification is primarily used as a connection between the FOODIE core application schema and the Transport application schema
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).

description of essential nutrients for plant growth or any other relevant nutrients, no matter whether in a form element (like phosphorus) or ion/molecule (like phosphorus pentoxide - P<sub>2</sub>O<sub>5</sub>)
designation under which the nutrient is commonly known
the value of a physical quantity of the nutrient, together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
textual description of a method for an estimation of the nutrient amount in the ManagementZone
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).

an extent in time limited by two instances (beginning and ending), e.g. between 2015-03-01 and 2015-09-30------------------------- <sup>1</sup> Note: TM_Period allows also undetermined periods like since 2015-02-25 or before 2015-02-25.
electrical conductivity as the ability of a material to conduct (transmit) an electrical current in soil

expression of the organic matter component of soil, consisting of plant and animal residues at various stages of decomposition, cells and tissues of soil organisms, and substances synthesized by soil organisms
a measurement of the level of acid or alkali in a solution or substance
determination of classes for agricultural soils based on their physical texture
expression of a different sizes of mineral particles in a particular sample
classification of a TreatmentPlan from the user point of view; any classification system may be used
unique identification of the TreatmentPlan from the user point of view
a brief narrative summary of the TreatmentPlan content and rationale
any further information related to the TreatmentPlan that may help for a better understanding
a period to which the TreatmentPlan was designed; typically a campaign may be an agronomical year or a season
date and time at which the Treatment was inserted in the database
unique identification of a CropSpecies according to the user (farmer)
designation under which the CropSpecies is commonly known
a principal taxonomic category that ranks above genus and below order
a principal taxonomic category that ranks above species and below family
a group of living organisms consisting of similar individuals capable of exchanging genes or interbreeding
a taxonomic category that ranks below subspecies (where present) or species, its members differing from others of the same subspecies or species in minor but permanent or heritable characteristics
a brief narrative summary of the CropSpecies content and rationale
any further information on crop species inserted by a user
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).
designation under which the Ingredient is commonly known
unique identification of an ActiveIngredient from the national or user point of view
the value of a physical quantity of applicable ActiveIngredient, together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
the minimum application rate of the Treatment
the maximum application rate of the Treatment
the value of a physical quantity of applied Treatment, together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
identification of the Treatment application in the form of a code list
rationale why the Treatment was used in the form of a code list
any further information related to the Treatment that may help for a better understanding
financial calculation of a compensation in return for goods and services used during the Treatment application

recommended speed for the application of the treatment that should be expressed together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103; it is recommended to use kmh-1 as a motionSpeed unit
recommended pressure for the application of the Treatment that should be expressed together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
indication whether a flow adjustment was needed for the application of the Treatment; should be expressed together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103

a width in which a machine is capable to apply the Treatment, should be expressed together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103; it is recommended to use meters (m) as an applicationWidth unit

the minimum (attribute minimumDose of the DoseUnit data type) and maximum (attribute maximumDose of the DoseUnit data type) application rate of the Treatment, should be expressed together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103; it is recommended to use kilograms (kg) or litres (l) per hectare as an areaDose unit
alerts automatically generated by models integrated in the FOODIE platform
unique identification of the Alert in the FOODIE platform
type of alert according to the user-defined classification, e.g. phytosanitary
a brief narrative summary of the Alert content and rationale
the geometry defining the spatial extent for which the Alert is applicable
date (and time) in which the Alert was created by the FOODIE platform
indication whether the user is aware of the alert or not (as a Boolean value: true/false)

unique identification of a tractive vehicle for the machine applying the treatment; such unique identification, e.g. TRCT00721, is primarily used as a connection between the FOODIE core application schema and the Transport application schema
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).
identification of the planted crop species
designation under which the CropSpecies is commonly known; such designation is expressed as the CropType data type
the geometry defining the spatial extent of the CropSpecies on the Plot
date (and time) when the CropSpecies started to exist in the real world
date (and time) since when the CropSpecies no longer exists in the real world
containing relevant production-related data, that is defined as a ProductionType data type
date and time at which this version of the CropSpecies was inserted or changed in the database
date and time at which this version of the CropSpecies was superseded or retired in the database
the basic feature type for any kind of application with explicitly defined geometry

type of the intervention, e.g. tillage or pruning as a free text since the common code list of all types of intervention was not feasible to provide, the types of intervention vary from country to country as well as from farmer to farmer
human readable description of the type of intervention which may be a sub-type of intervention or a broader description intended for the common understanding of the intervention
any further information on intervention inserted by a user
identification of a tractive vehicle for the machine applying the treatment, that is defined as a TractorType data type
identification of a machine applying the treatment, that is defined as a MachineType data type

status of the intervention, e.g. approved, pending, completed as a free text since the common code list of all statuses of intervention was not feasible to provide, the statuses and naming of an Intervention vary according to the type of an Intervention as well as from farmer to farmer
financial calculation of a compensation in return for goods and services used during the Intervention
a person or a body who has the power and authority to give instructions and guarantee the conducted Intervention
identification (typically at least name and surname) of a person(s) who has conducted an Intervention
a person or a body who inserted the Intervention into the database
the geometry defining the spatial extent of the Intervention
date and time at which the Intervention was inserted in the database
date (and time) when the Intervention started in the real world
date (and time) when the Intervention ended in the real world
designation under which the productionProperty is commonly known
quantitative property that is being estimated by the analysis, together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
qualitative property that is being estimated by the analysis expressed as a free text
type of a property that is being estimated by the analysis
date (and time) at which the analysis of production was conducted
unique identification of the Product from the user point of view
designation under which the Product is commonly known

type of the Product, e.g. pesticide, as a free text since the common code list of all types of Product was not feasible to provide, the types of Product vary from country to country as well as from farmer to farmer

more detailed classification of a type of the Product, e.g. biochemical insecticide, as a free text since the common code list of all sub-types of Product was not feasible to provide, the sub-types of Product vary from country to country as well as from farmer to farmer
origin of a product in the form of a code list comprising the following values: organic and mineral
a brief narrative summary of the Product
identification of a producer of the Product
information on safe manipulation with the Product
information on the safe storage of the Product
unique identification of a product according to the national or any other relevant registration scheme
link to the national or any other relevant register where the Product was registered
financial calculation of a compensation in return for the used amount of the Product
identification of nutrients, i.e. chemical elements and compounds, that are necessary for plant growth
designation under which the nutrient is commonly known
the value of a physical quantity of the nutrient, together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
textual description of a method for an estimation of the nutrient amount in the Product
area with high-level information for decision makers in agriculture production
unique identification of the ManagementZone in the FOODIE platform
the basic mechanism for describing any property of a Soil
any further information on a management zone inserted by a user
the geometry defining the spatial extent of the ManagementZone
date (and time) when the ManagementZone started to exist in the real world
date (and time) since when the ManagementZone no longer exists in the real world
date and time at which this version of the ManagementZone was inserted or changed in the database
date and time at which this version of the ManagementZone was superseded or retired in the database
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).

unique identification of a Plot within the FOODIE platform; it is defined as an Identifier data type, i.e. a data type composed of a code (e.g. 178646A64BF), code space (MyFarm) and version in the form of date and time according to the ISO 8601 standard (e.g. version 2015-02-18T18:09:07)
free text description of a Plot from a user point of view
origin of a Plot when taking into consideration only two options: manual (created by human user) and system (produced by the FOODIE platform)
the geometry defining the spatial extent of the Plot
date (and time) when the Plot started to exist in the real world
date (and time) since when the Plot no longer exists in the real world
date and time at which this version of the Plot was inserted or changed in the database
date and time at which this version of the Plot was superseded or retired in the database
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).
date and time at which the information on production was inserted or changed in the database
an assemblage of cultivated individuals which are distinguished by any characters (morphological, physiological, cytological, chemical or others) significant for the purposes of agriculture
the value of a physical quantity of produced variety, together with its unit according to the Measure data type as defined in ISO/TS 19103
the basic mechanism for describing any property of a Production, that is defined as a PropertyType data type
At least one of the function attributes of the Holding spatial object shall be provided using the EconomicActivityNACEValue code list (for the activity attribute of the Function data type).
